\begin_layout Standard
The physician must then make his decision about 
\begin_inset Formula $t$
\end_inset

 about 
\begin_inset Formula $\gamma$
\end_inset

 sequentially.
 First the physician chooses a quantity of information 
\begin_inset Formula $\gamma$
\end_inset

 and then chooses a treatment that maximizes expected utility.
 However, as information cannot be returned, the physician must base his
 decision of 
\begin_inset Formula $\gamma$
\end_inset

 on the maximization of 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "eq:expected-posterior"

\end_inset

 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
u(t,\theta,\gamma)=\mathbb{E}[u(t,s,x)]=\max_{\gamma}\left[\int_{X}\max_{t}\int_{a}^{b}u(t,s)dF^{\gamma}(x\mid s)dF^{\gamma}(x)dsdx-C(\gamma)\right]\label{eq:expected-posterior}
\end{equation}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
now the first order conditions of expected utility gives that 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{eqnarray*}
\int_{X}\int_{a}^{b}u(t,s)\left[f(s\mid x,\gamma)f_{\gamma}(x,\gamma)+f_{\gamma}(s\mid x,\gamma)f(s,\theta)\right]dsdx & = & C_{\gamma}(\gamma)\\
\int_{X}\int_{a}^{b}u_{t}(t,s)f(s\mid x,\gamma)f(x,\gamma)dsdx & = & 0
\end{eqnarray*}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection
Case 1: a change in severity of illness
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
An increase in the severity of illness can be archived by shifting the patients
 distribution of 
\begin_inset Formula $d$
\end_inset

 to the right.
 let 
\begin_inset Formula $\Delta$
\end_inset

 be the distance by which the distribution is shifted and leave all other
 moments of the distribution unchanged.
 Then let 
\begin_inset Formula $f(s,\theta)=q(s-\Delta,\theta)$
\end_inset

, so that the distribution of 
\begin_inset Formula $f$
\end_inset

 is simply the distribution of 
\begin_inset Formula $q$
\end_inset

 shifted to the right by the distance 
\begin_inset Formula $\Delta$
\end_inset

 for all 
\begin_inset Formula $s$
\end_inset

.
 Then I can write 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
u(t,\theta,\gamma)=\mathbb{E}[u(t,s,x)]=\max_{\gamma}\left[\int_{X}\max_{t}\left\{ \int_{a}^{b}u(t,s)f(s\mid x,\gamma)ds\right\} f(x,\gamma)dx-C(\gamma)\right]
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

